    {
        "content": "<p>the way to avoid this entirely would be to rather assume <code>N' : Submodule R M</code> and <code>hN' : N' ≤ N</code>. if that's not possible, you will possibly rather want to talk about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.map#doc\">docs#Submodule.map</a> combined with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.subtype#doc\">docs#Submodule.subtype</a></p>",
        "id": 468594307,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1725811555
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that should give you <code>N'.map (N.subtype) = P</code> as a statement to prove</p>",
        "id": 468595382,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1725812054
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"684366\">Edward van de Meent</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Casting.20subgroups.2Fsubmodules/near/468594307\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the way to avoid this entirely would be to rather assume <code>N' : Submodule R M</code> and <code>hN' : N' ⊆ N</code>. if that's not possible, you will possibly rather want to talk about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.map#doc\">docs#Submodule.map</a> combined with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.subtype#doc\">docs#Submodule.subtype</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>hN' : N' ≤ N</code> is preferred here</p>",
        "id": 468640830,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1725838251
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"684366\">Edward van de Meent</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Casting.20subgroups.2Fsubmodules/near/468594307\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the way to avoid this entirely would be to rather assume <code>N' : Submodule R M</code> and <code>hN' : N' ⊆ N</code>. if that's not possible, you will possibly rather want to talk about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.map#doc\">docs#Submodule.map</a> combined with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Submodule.subtype#doc\">docs#Submodule.subtype</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In my case, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>N</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is given as the kernel of a map so I can't use your first suggestion.  Following your second suggestion, I was able to define the inclusion from N' to N and from N to M, define the composition, and then take the range.</p>",
        "id": 468698379,
        "sender_full_name": "Jarod Alper",
        "timestamp": 1725865623
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Casting.20subgroups.2Fsubmodules/near/468640830\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>hN' : N' ≤ N</code> is preferred here</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, it's silly Lean doesn't recognize <code>N' ⊆ N</code>.  There should at least be a linter that recognizes this mistake.  I'm sure that I had learned in some Lean tutorials to write <code>N' ≤ N</code>, but I guess I had forgotten and it took me 15 minutes the other day debugging an error to realize that this was the problem.</p>",
        "id": 468699727,
        "sender_full_name": "Jarod Alper",
        "timestamp": 1725866028
    }
]